citeinfo.title: Master Street Address Guide Community Boundaries Massachusetts 2013

descript.abstract: This polygon dataset represents community boundaries in Massachusetts. The datalayer represents Master Street Address Guide(MSAG) community boundaries created from the MassGIS Community Boundaries (Towns) From Survey Points layer, the assigned MSAG community values in the NAVSTREETS layer, and parcel data (where available).
descript.purpose: This dataset is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows Vista Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.4000

attracc.attraccr: There have been no deliberate or intentional omissions or inclusions of polygon attributes within this data set.

horizpa.horizpar:
Curt Crowe (the National Geodetic Survey's liason to Massachusetts) has stated the following concerning the TOWNSURVEY_POLYM layer: "these are not survey quality coordinates. The atlas coordinates were only published to the nearest foot on an early datum and the survey work was done over a thirty year span. The conversion updated the coordinates but it did not improve their accuracy. I would expect these values to be good to within 3 feet (1 meter) in most cases. Some areas will be slightly better and some could be much worse."
The inside MSAG boundaries are estimates based on assignment of MSAG community to segments in a street layer plus parcel polygons where available and appropriate. These boundaries are not official.

attr.attrdef: Emergency Service Number (ESN). Defined as a three to five digit number representing a unique combination of emergency service agencies (Law Enforcement, Fire, and Emergency Medical Service) designated to serve a specific range of addresses within a particular geographical area, or Emergency Service Zone (ESZ). The ESN facilitates selective routing and selective transfer, if required, to the appropriate PSAP and the dispatching of the proper service agency (ies).
